</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PAY REVIEW bodies and Whitley Councils, which cover workers including nurses
and teachers, should be abolished so that a truly social market can operate,
says a pamphlet published today by the Social Market Foundation, an
independent think-tank.
Despite a decade of liberalisation in the private sector the pay of 90 per
