FT  18 OCT 93 / Builders report no September upturn
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE HOUSING market failed to show its normal seasonal upturn in September,
figures released by the House Builders Federation show today.
Just 10 per cent more housebuilders reported an improvement in net
reservations than reported a decline, in what is usually one of the best
months for the housing market.
