FT  18 OCT 93 / The Old and New Lloyd's (circa 1989)
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Old Lloyd's (circa 1989)
Capital provided by 30,000-plus Names with unlimited liability
Organised into more than 400 syndicates by
More than 200 agents
Lloyd's Corporation administers and regulates market but
stands back from its commercial operations
THE NEW LLOYD'S (circa 1994)
Capital provided by
17,000 individual Names with unlimited liability, many
spreading their risks across the market through so-called
MAPA arrangements;
institutional and retail investors backing investment trusts
and companies, some of them listed on Stock Exchange
Number of syndicates cut to 150
Fewer than 100 agents
Lloyd's Corporation plays more active role in enforcing professional
standards in market, developing strategy and controlling costs
