<DATELINE>
   SANTIAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
LATIN AMERICAN leaders are to write to President Bill Clinton urging the US
Congress to approve the North American Free Trade Agreement. Failure to do
so, they will say, would be a bleak omen for US policy towards the
continent.
The decision to send the letter, to be drafted by Chile's President Patricio
