Rio Group of Latin American and Caribbean states.
Leaders see Nafta as a vital first stage in building a regional trading
bloc, regarded as an insurance policy against possible failure of the Gatt
global trade talks. 'Nafta is a first step towards creating a huge free
trade zone spanning the continent,' said President Cesar Gaviria of
Colombia.
