<HEADLINE>
FT  18 OCT 93 / Delors fears EC is drifting towards break-up
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
EUROPEAN Commission President Jacques Delors said yesterday he feared the
European Community was drifting towards becoming a soulless free-trade area
and ultimately a slow break-up, Reuter reports from Paris.
Despite the ratification of the Maastricht treaty on European union, calling
for a common foreign policy and a single currency by 1999, a gloomy Mr
Delors saw no sign of a revival of the 12-nation Community.
'What I see is European construction drifting towards a free trade zone,
that is to say an English-style Europe, which I reject,' Mr Delors, a French
Socialist, said on Radio Luxembourg. 'If we do nothing, this drift will lead
in 15 years to a break-up (of the EC).'
