<HEADLINE>
FT  16 OCT 93 / Finance and the Family: Eurotunnel needs another Pounds 1bn
 -At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Eurotunnel confirmed this week that it would need to raise at least another
Pounds 1bn from banks and shareholders by mid-May 1994. At least half the
additional funds will come from a rights issue. The company has reduced its
initial revenue estimates because of start-up delays and price competition
from the ferry companies. On current estimates, it will not be until 1998
that the company breaks even on a cash basis.
