FT  16 OCT 93 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The pimento market was firm on increased buying interest from central
europe, reports Man Producten. Spot supplies in Europe were very limited.
Mexican supplies were offered at USDollars 1,850 a tonne, cif, while
Jamaicans were unchanged at Dollars 2,300 for spot and Dollars 2,100 for
shipment. Madagascan cloves were at a premium with Dollars 925 a tonne
charged for cif supplies and Dollars 1,000 for spot. Indonesian cassia
prices were unchanged with VA/KA sticks at Dollars 2,400 spot, and Dollars
2,300 afloat. Seychelles spot supplies were not available with new arrivals
awaited from local suppliers.
